ce:section.ce:para:
Chiral CDs were synthesized using L/D-Asp as the carbon and chiral source via a rapid microwave-assisted one-step reaction (Scheme 1
                           ). The morphology and structure of the prepared chiral CDs were investigated using TEM (Fig. 1A
                            and 1B) and XRD (Fig. 1C and 1D) measurements. As displayed from the TEM image, the size of L-Asp-CDs was mainly distributed in the range of 2–4 nm, while the size of D-Asp-CDs was mainly distributed in the range of 1–3 nm. XRD showed that both diffraction peaks were in the range of 21.30°–24.25° and corresponded to a graphitic structure. Both diffraction peaks were broader, which was mainly due to the small size of the prepared chiral CDs [28–30]. The interlayer spacing was 0.42 nm and 0.41 nm for L-Asp-CDs and D-Asp-CDs, respectively.
